measure.name: report_simulation_output
measure.description: Reports simulation outputs for residential HPXML-based models.
measure.modeler_description: Processes EnergyPlus simulation outputs in order to generate an annual output file and an optional timeseries output file.

argument.name: output_format
argument.description: The file format of the annual (and timeseries, if requested) outputs. If 'csv_dview' is selected, the timeseries CSV file will include header rows that facilitate opening the file in the DView application.

argument.name: include_annual_total_consumptions
argument.description: Generates annual energy consumptions for the total building.

argument.name: include_annual_fuel_consumptions
argument.description: Generates annual energy consumptions for each fuel type.

argument.name: include_annual_end_use_consumptions
argument.display_name: Generate Annual Output: End Use Consumptions
argument.description: Generates annual energy consumptions for each end use.

argument.name: include_annual_system_use_consumptions
argument.display_name: Generate Annual Output: System Use Consumptions
argument.description: Generates annual energy consumptions for each end use of each HVAC and water heating system.

argument.name: include_annual_emissions
argument.description: Generates annual emissions. Requires the appropriate HPXML inputs to be specified.

argument.name: include_annual_emission_fuels
argument.display_name: Generate Annual Output: Emission Fuel Uses
argument.description: Generates annual emissions for each fuel type. Requires the appropriate HPXML inputs to be specified.

argument.name: include_annual_emission_end_uses
argument.display_name: Generate Annual Output: Emission End Uses
argument.description: Generates annual emissions for each end use. Requires the appropriate HPXML inputs to be specified.

argument.name: include_annual_total_loads
argument.description: Generates annual heating, cooling, and hot water loads.

argument.name: include_annual_unmet_hours
argument.description: Generates annual unmet hours for heating and cooling.

argument.name: include_annual_peak_fuels
argument.description: Generates annual electricity peaks for summer/winter.

argument.name: include_annual_peak_loads
argument.description: Generates annual peak loads for heating/cooling.

argument.name: include_annual_component_loads
argument.description: Generates annual heating and cooling loads disaggregated by component type.

argument.name: include_annual_hot_water_uses
argument.display_name: Generate Annual Output: Hot Water Uses
argument.description: Generates annual hot water usages for each end use.

argument.name: include_annual_hvac_summary
argument.description: Generates HVAC capacities, design temperatures, and design loads.

argument.name: include_annual_resilience
argument.description: Generates annual resilience outputs.

argument.name: timeseries_frequency
argument.description: The frequency at which to report timeseries output data. Using 'none' will disable timeseries outputs.

argument.name: include_timeseries_total_consumptions
argument.description: Generates timeseries energy consumptions for the total building.

argument.name: include_timeseries_fuel_consumptions
argument.description: Generates timeseries energy consumptions for each fuel type.

argument.name: include_timeseries_end_use_consumptions
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: End Use Consumptions
argument.description: Generates timeseries energy consumptions for each end use.

argument.name: include_timeseries_system_use_consumptions
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: System Use Consumptions
argument.description: Generates timeseries energy consumptions for each end use of each HVAC and water heating system.

argument.name: include_timeseries_emissions
argument.description: Generates timeseries emissions. Requires the appropriate HPXML inputs to be specified.

argument.name: include_timeseries_emission_fuels
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: Emission Fuel Uses
argument.description: Generates timeseries emissions for each fuel type. Requires the appropriate HPXML inputs to be specified.

argument.name: include_timeseries_emission_end_uses
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: Emission End Uses
argument.description: Generates timeseries emissions for each end use. Requires the appropriate HPXML inputs to be specified.

argument.name: include_timeseries_hot_water_uses
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: Hot Water Uses
argument.description: Generates timeseries hot water usages for each end use.

argument.name: include_timeseries_total_loads
argument.description: Generates timeseries heating, cooling, and hot water loads.

argument.name: include_timeseries_component_loads
argument.description: Generates timeseries heating and cooling loads disaggregated by component type.

argument.name: include_timeseries_unmet_hours
argument.description: Generates timeseries unmet hours for heating and cooling.

argument.name: include_timeseries_zone_temperatures
argument.description: Generates timeseries temperatures for each thermal zone.

argument.name: include_timeseries_airflows
argument.description: Generates timeseries airflows.

argument.name: include_timeseries_weather
argument.description: Generates timeseries weather data.

argument.name: include_timeseries_resilience
argument.description: Generates timeseries resilience outputs.

argument.name: timeseries_timestamp_convention
argument.description: Determines whether timeseries timestamps use the start-of-period or end-of-period convention. Doesn't apply if the output format is 'csv_dview'.

argument.name: timeseries_num_decimal_places
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: Number of Decimal Places
argument.description: Allows overriding the default number of decimal places for timeseries output. Does not apply if output format is msgpack, where no rounding is performed because there is no file size penalty to storing full precision.

argument.name: add_timeseries_dst_column
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: Add TimeDST Column
argument.description: Optionally add, in addition to the default local standard Time column, a local clock TimeDST column. Requires that daylight saving time is enabled.

argument.name: add_timeseries_utc_column
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: Add TimeUTC Column
argument.description: Optionally add, in addition to the default local standard Time column, a local clock TimeUTC column. If the time zone UTC offset is not provided in the HPXML file, the time zone in the EPW header will be used.

argument.name: user_output_variables
argument.display_name: Generate Timeseries Output: EnergyPlus Output Variables
argument.description: Optionally generates timeseries EnergyPlus output variables. If multiple output variables are desired, use a comma-separated list. Do not include key values; by default all key values will be requested. Example: "Zone People Occupant Count, Zone People Total Heating Energy"

argument.name: annual_output_file_name
argument.description: If not provided, defaults to 'results_annual.csv' (or 'results_annual.json' or 'results_annual.msgpack').

argument.name: timeseries_output_file_name
argument.description: If not provided, defaults to 'results_timeseries.csv' (or 'results_timeseries.json' or 'results_timeseries.msgpack').
